title: Jimmy Buffett looks at Amway Center appearance - Orlando Sentinel - Orlando Sentinel
text:
Jimmy Buffett looks at Amway Center appearance Jimmy Buffett Charles Sykes / Charles Sykes/Invision/AP   May 13 at Amway Center in Orlando as part of his "I Don't Know Tour."   May 13 at Amway Center in Orlando as part of his "I Don't Know Tour." (Charles Sykes / Charles Sykes/Invision/AP) Trevor Fraser .
The perpetual money machine and Parrothead cult leader (and occasional songwriter) is on his “I Don’t Know Tour,” a reference to the chorus of his 1979 hit song “Volcano” and his answer to the question, “How much tequila is too much?” 
Buffett, 71, has been touring for 42 years (and could have grown a pencil-thin mustache at any time during that period and hasn’t). He’s also working on getting even more mileage out of his biggest song with a new musical entitled “Escape to Margaritaville,” slated to open in May in California. 
This year also marks the 40th anniversary for his album “Changes in Latitudes, Changes in Attitudes.” Dancing aunts and uncles at weddings everywhere presumably thank him. 
Fruitcakes can catch Buffett on May 13. Tickets are $38-$132.50, on sale Friday, Feb. 24. Details at ticketmaster.com .
